| Incident | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| Vietnam War | During the Vietnam War, Singapore maintained neutrality despite pressure from both the United States and North Vietnam. It provided humanitarian aid and hosted peace talks. |
| ASEAN Diplomacy | Singapore has mediated regional disputes among ASEAN member states, demonstrating neutrality in conflicts over territorial disputes and political tensions. |
| Middle East Peace Process | Singapore has supported peace efforts in the Middle East by offering neutral ground for dialogues and peace talks between conflicting parties. |
| South China Sea Disputes | Singapore advocates for peaceful resolution of South China Sea disputes through international law and diplomacy, maintaining neutrality in complex territorial claims. |
| Global Diplomatic Relations | Singapore's foreign policy emphasizes neutrality to maintain diplomatic ties with countries across different political and ideological spectrums, facilitating international diplomacy and trade. |
